Jack Johnson Crowd Run
docs.creator: Tyler
docs.description: On August 28, 2004 I attended the San Diego Street Scene music festival. I was audio taping various acts and decided to stay till the end of the Foo Fighters. Upon their completion, I sprinted to the extreme opposite end of the festival grounds to hear Jack Johnson play. Though I was late, hit 'record' as I approached the stage area. This recording is the 2 minutes or so that were recorded from when i entered the general stage area to when I finally reached my final taping spot near the stage. Because the microphones I use to tape shows are 'caroid' (directional) and because the grounds were so densely packed with people, I was sprinting and weaving through crowds and conversations. This recording juts through soundwaves and it is interesting to hear the snippets of people's converstaions as I sprint through the crowd.

An Eileen Myles lecture, "Friendship: the force of community in poetry and prose." Myles discusses the role of friendship and poetry in bringing one's inner world, which she likens to the world of her early friendships with women, to the outer world, which she relates to her early friendships with men. She discusses the growing laterality of the art world and emphasizes the defining importance of context.

docs.description: Setlist: 1) Intro/Tuning (not included), 2) All I Need > Apt 54 (2nd half), 3) Sultans of Swing [Dire Straits], 4) (Gotta) Move Out, 5) The Interrogation... Zmick plays a brief set on a Saturday evening to warm up the crowd for Cornmeal at the 2008 Urbana Sweet Corn Festval. The setlist includes a Dire Straits cover, along with a trio of Zmick originals - not to mention the slap bass solo of "Apt 54" from Dan Wonsover. Lead vocals performed by drummer, Kris Ahrens ("All I Need") and guitarist Brad Miller ("Gotta Move Out" & "Interrogation"). Special thanks to rhinowing for uploading the flac files to etree. I converted them to mp3. PLEASE SHARE - NEVER SELL. Zmick supports taping/trading of their concerts.
